.\" Manpage for tbw
.TH TBW 1 "2026-02-23" "5.1.0" "tbw manual"
.SH NAME
tbw \- calculate SSD Terabytes Written (TBW)
.SH SYNOPSIS
tbw [--bytes] [-v] <device>...
.SH DESCRIPTION
`tbw` reads SMART data from SATA and NVMe drives and calculates total bytes written (TBW).
Default output is decimal terabytes (TB). Use `--bytes` for raw bytes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
--bytes
Output raw bytes written instead of TB
.TP
-v
Verbose output: shows device, type, bytes, and TB
.TP
-h, --help
Show help
.TP
-V
Show version
.SH EXAMPLES
tbw sda
tbw --bytes /dev/nvme0n1
tbw -v sda nvme0n1
.SH SEE ALSO
smartctl(8), jq(1)
